    "communications_language": "en_US",
    "description": "Bemax Arena is a modern multifunctional sports hall located within the Morača Sports Centre in Podgorica, Montenegro. Originally built as an indoor swimming pool in 1983, it was completely reconstructed and reopened in 2019 as a state-of-the-art arena with over 2,200 seats. In 2025/2026, a partnership between Padel Montenegro and Bemax Arena was signed to build four new padel courts of the highest quality, suitable for both recreational players and competitive athletes. The facility already includes a modern gym (Arena Gym), outdoor basketball courts, teqball tables, and hosts various sports events, concerts, and tournaments. The new padel courts aim to further boost the padel community in Montenegro, with plans for tournaments, leagues, and children's padel schools. The arena is located in the new part of Podgorica, on the right bank of the Morača River."
  },
